OL,3,C17-year-old arrested in connection to
OL,4,Ccat deaths in Carlisle
OL,6,FA 17-year-old from Carlisle has been
OL,7,Farrested following reports of three
OL,8,Fseparate cat deaths in the city.
OL,10,FCumbria Police arrested the teenager
OL,11,Fon Friday 29 May on suspicion of
OL,12,Foffences related to animal cruelty.
OL,13,FThe force said they had received
OL,14,Freports of cat deaths in the Richmond
OL,15,FGreen and Raffles areas of Carlisle.
OL,17,FPolice say it is suspected the cats
OL,18,Fwere attacked by dogs. Officers also
OL,19,Fconfirmed a "lurcher-type dog" has
OL,20,Fbeen seised from an address in
OL,21,FCarlisle.
